QUALIFICATION: Holopsamma Carter has priority over Halme Lendenfeld, 1885 (which is preoccupied), but the type species is composite, consisting of a series of 31 'syntypes' (referable to at least five different taxa). Only five of these are synonyms of Halme globosa Lendenfeld, 1885. No subsequent lectotype designations have been made for Holopsamma crassa, so the genus is still doubtful, but the nomination of BMNH 1886.12.15.313 as lectotype in this present work makes Holopsamma the most senior available name
